.SH APPLICATION USAGE
.LP
Some implementationz of \fIcatopen\fP() use \fImalloc\fP() ta allocate
space for
internal buffer areas. Da \fIcatopen\fP() function may fail if there
is insufficient storage space available ta accommodate these
buffers.
.LP
Conformin applications must assume dat message catalog descriptors
are not valid afta a cold-ass lil call ta one of tha \fIexec\fP functions.
.LP
Application writas should be aware dat guidelines fo' tha location
of message catalogs aint yet been pimped. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Therefore
they should take care ta avoid conflictin wit catalogs used by other
applications n' tha standard utilities.
